BIOSAMPLE_COLLECT_METH_DESC: The use of the Ponar grab sampler or Petite Ponar grab sampler provides a quantitative sample of soft sediments in rivers or lakes. The sampler is designed to penetrate the substrate by its own weight and enclose a portion of the bottom by means of a gravity-activated closing mechanism. The standard Ponar measures nine inches on each side, enclosing a surface area of 0.56 square feet (0.052 square meters). The Petite Ponar measures six inches on each side, enclosing a surface area of 0.25 square feet (0.023 square meters).
